  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This pilot project integrates school-based mass treatment of soil-transmitted helminths with school feeding programs, strengthening and improving the outcomes of each with the addition of on-site balanced, healthy food production through aquaponics. The aquaponics component will also facilitate complementary preventive health, hygiene, nutrition, and food safety education among sudents, teachers, food preparers, and parents to mobilize broad-based community participation and encourage knowledge transfer and positive behaviour change.</narrative>
  </description>
